👯‍♀️ Here are some things NOT to say to twins part 2. Part 1 is PINNED 📍 to our page.

“If I Pinch You, Does Your Twin Feel It?” 
For some reason, people find this a fascinating concept—the idea that when one twin experiences a stimulus, the other twin will have a physical reaction to the sensation. Not only do they ask us this question, but they want to test out the theory by pinching or hitting one of us. 😅 Please don’t… 

“Can You Read Each Other’s Mind?”
One of the magical mysteries associated with multiples is that they share a physic connection. While the twin bond is a special aspect of our unique relationship, we were not endowed with extraordinary supernatural qualities.
We know each other very well and tend to have similar thought patterns, we’ve spent almost everyday together since conception what can you expect?

“You’re basically the same person” 
While there are no denying our similarities, We have differences in our personalities, our hobbies, our style, and in our life experiences. As a twin, it can be difficult to form your own identity and to have your peers recognize it. Having someone say you are like “the same person” — even if it’s in a joking manner — only reinforces the misconception that twins are not individuals.

“Do you do EVERYTHING together?” 
No. And sometimes yes. Every set of twins is different. We could talk in detail about the different types of twins. In psychology there’s actually type A,B, and C twins. But us personally, no. We do A LOT together. We used to share a car so it made the most amount of sense to work most of our gigs together, but we also do things by ourselves. We work individually. We run errands individually. Don’t get me wrong, we prefer the company. We’re both used to being around each other a lot so being alone alone is still a weird concept and we’d rather be around friends than be alone alone. 

“Twins are weird.”
You might think this is an unlikely statement to make in a conversation with a twin, but it’s been said to us quite a few times especially in the industry we work in. Really it’s just like- you’re calling what we are and can’t control weird like it’s a bad thing- why? #twins #reels

Not because, “oh we want our babies to be genetically siblings.” But because we thought another set of identical twins would perfectly understand the relationship we have with each other, because they themselves have gone through similar experiences. When we watched The Suite Life of Zack and Cody (which we were obsessed with 😍) @autumn_m_read boyfriend was Zack and @rachel_a_read was Cody. 𝐍𝐄𝐖 Dermadry Device to treat our Hyperhidrosis 🚫 💦 
 
If your new to our page; welcome! If you’ve been following us for a while you’re familiar with a condition we have called Hyperhidrosis. Which is, “Abnormally excessive sweating involving the extremities, underarms, and face and is unrelated to temperature, stress, or exercise.” We have excessive sweating in our hands and our feet. 
It has affected our day-to-day lives in small and big ways since we can remember, we’ve had untreated and undiagnosed hyperhidrosis since we were in middle school. 
 
Dermadry is a company based out of Canada, and we found them two years ago when we went to a special dermatologist in ATL, and she prescribed it for us!  We’ve been using our @Dermadry treatment for 3 years now, and we can say it’s such a game changer, especially with this 𝐍𝐄𝐖 device they’ve sent us! We do our treatment 2/3 times biweekly and have been for 3 years! 
 
We’re happy to be vocal about it and to share a product that has worked so well for us and given us lasting results. This device has a 98.3% success rate, so we’re not shocked. @dermadry is also having a 60% OFF discount right at checkout!

Being a TWIN is like… 👯‍♀️ 
⬇️ ⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️
Accepting the reality that people will mix us up and get our names wrong everyday for the rest of our lives. We don’t mind being called twin if it’s for a quick job we completely understand!

Always getting stared at in public.. even when we don’t dress alike. We could be grocery shopping or running daily errands in completely different attire and sometimes we’ll be asked multiple times in one location, “if we are twins” or just stared at. 

Constantly being compared to each other. Why does it need to be a comparison? Why does one have to be lesser then the other? We don’t like to be compared—favorably or unfavorably. Like us for who we are, not for how we stack up against each other.

Difficultly dating - for many reasons. A lot of people are looking for “the one” or their “soulmate”. We were born with our soulmate. Partners expect to have the same connection that we have with our twin and that’s not going to happen. We’ve each been told we have ridiculously high standards. But when you think about it- we keep each other company everyday, we enjoy the same activities, foods, hobbies, fun, and more. So unless a partner will be adding value to our lives - why bother?!

Do you remember those whimsical dreams we had as children? 🧜‍♀️ The ones that seemed so far-fetched, yet sparked an undeniable sense of wonder within us? One such dream that captivated our hearts from the earliest years was the longing to be a mermaid. The enchantment of the sea, the allure of its mysteries, and the graceful elegance of mermaids held an irresistible charm. ✨ 

As kids, we would spend hours with our flippers and extra large leggings we used as tails in the lake creating adventures gliding effortlessly through the underwater world and envisioning ourselves with a mesmerizing tail.

It’s fascinating how dreams have the power to shape our lives.
Years later, we never stopped wanting to be a mermaid. As we got older, despite being told, “we were too old for such things” we just got more invested and crafted mermaid tops and crowns and accessories and now we have 3 beautiful tails from @finfolkproductions 

We’ve gotten to swim and collaborate with fellow merfolk like @mermaid_nikki 😍 and through this extraordinary experience, we learned that dreams are not merely figments of our imagination but manifestations of our deepest desires. They are the seeds of possibility, waiting to be nurtured by unwavering belief and persistence.

Dream on, dear friends, and let your dreams lead you to a world where anything is possible. 🌟✨🧜‍♀️
